Speaker 1: Good morning, Miss! Nice day, isn't it?
Speaker 2: Good morning! It sure is, I think it's supposed to stay sunny all day. 
Speaker 1: That's great. I hope it stays this way for the weekend. Planning to do some yard work.
Speaker 2: Yeah, I noticed your garden is always well-kept. I suppose it's a lot of hard work?
Speaker 1: You could say so, but it's more of a hobby for me. Helps me unwind after a long day of coding. 
Speaker 2: Oh, you work in IT, right?
Speaker 1: Yes, I'm a software engineer. Been working for a startup in Berlin for the past few years. 
Speaker 2: That sounds interesting. I've always been fascinated by technology, but I'm more into the biological sciences. 
Speaker 1: Really? Are you studying, or...?
Speaker 2: Yes, I'm doing my masters in neuroscience at Salem State. It's challenging but I really enjoy it.
Speaker 1: Neuroscience, huh? That's impressive. Must be quite complex.
Speaker 2: It is, but it's also fascinating. For instance, did you know that the human brain has around 86 billion neurons?
Speaker 1: Wow, that's a lot. I can't even begin to comprehend that. I guess it's like trying to understand the billions of lines of code that make up a complex software.
Speaker 2: Exactly, it's all about understanding patterns and connections, whether it's in the brain or in code. 
Speaker 1: I never thought of it that way, but you're right. It's interesting how the principles can be similar across different fields.
Speaker 2: Yeah, it's all a matter of perspective.
Speaker 1: Anyway, I'll let you get on with your day. It was nice talking to you, Miss.
Speaker 2: Same here, have a nice day and good luck with your garden this weekend!
Speaker 1: Thanks, good luck with your studies too!
Speaker 2: Thank you. Have a great day!
